episodes.title: Taking a Chance! The Two Arms Go into Battle!
episodes.plot: Zoro gets back on his feet and along with Sanji, confronts King and Queen, the Lead Performers of the Animal Kingdom Pirates. Watching Zoro fight, Hyogoro and Kawamatsu remember someone from way back.

episodes.title: Rise to Dawn! The Peach Colored Dragon Rages!
episodes.plot: Dogstorm confronts his sworn enemy who destroyed his country. Meanwhile, Cat Viper faces Perospero who is responsible for Pedro's death. At Tokage Port, Momonosuke roars with his determined eyes.

episodes.title: For the Future! Yamato and the Great Swordsmen's Pledge!
episodes.plot: The battle between Kaido and Yamato gets intense. Backed into a corner, Yamato remembers three great swordsmen who he met when he was a child. Their stunning choice for the future of the Land of Wano encourages Yamato.

episodes.title: Luffy Soars! Revenge Against the King of the Beasts!
episodes.plot: Luffy amps up the reluctant Momonosuke, who is afraid of heights, in his giant pink dragon form, to fly and take him to Onigashima in the sky. Meanwhile, Yamato, in a hard battle against Kaido, vows to survive until Luffy returns

episodes.title: Two Dragons Face Off! Momonosuke's Determination!
episodes.plot: Momonosuke faces Kaido once again trembling in fear. However, with Luffy's encouragement, he bravely steps up and shows his dragon fangs remembering what he had to go through because of Kaido.

episodes.title: A Legend All Over Again! Luffy's Fist Roars in the Sky
episodes.plot: Momonosuke once again gets cold feet, but this time, he has a reliable ally who can teach him how to fly. The clash between Luffy and Kaido shakes up the sky and enables Dogstorm and Cat Viper to exert all their strength.

episodes.title: The Situation Has Grown Tense! The End of Onigashima!
episodes.plot: Realizing Onigashima's impending threat, imperiling everyone's life, Yamato and Momonosuke launch a secret operation. Meanwhile, Sanji and Zoro are both in a deadly battle against Queen and King

episodes.title: Sanji's Mutation - The Two Arms in Crisis!
episodes.plot: Queen's unforeseen move stuns everyone on the Performance Floor. And then, he goes on to utilize another special technique which can break every bone in Sanji's body. On the verge of a crisis, Sanji feels something strange again.

episodes.title: Death to Your Partner! Killer's Deadly Gamble!
episodes.plot: Killer tries to figure out how to fight against Hawkins whose power enables him to transfer damage against him to Kid. Kid is dying not knowing where his damage is coming from. Killer takes a chance with Kid's life on the line.

episodes.title: A Shadowy Figure Pulls the Strings! Onigashima in Flames
episodes.plot: Sanji still wonders what is happening to his body as he receives attacks. Meanwhile, the dying Kin'emon hears an unexpected voice calling for the also dying Kanjuro.

episodes.title: A Countercharge! Law and Kid's Return-Attack Combination
episodes.plot: Law and Kid are having a tough battle against Big Mom. However, when they decide to work collaboratively and use their awakened Devil Fruit powers, they see the possibility of taking down the old generation.

episodes.title: For Luffy - Sanji and Zoro's Oath
episodes.plot: Sanji is tormented by the idea of becoming a cruel Germa warrior like his siblings and torn between being strong or being humane as he is now. When he makes up his mind, he asks Zoro the ultimate favor.

episodes.title: The Onslaught of Kazenbo: Orochi's Evil Clutches Close in
episodes.plot: Kazenbo rampages through the castle creating panic among both the Animal Kingdom Pirates and the samurai. Orochi who is watching in excitement suddenly hears a sound that brings back memories.

episodes.title: Zoro's Hardship - A Monster! King the Wildfire
episodes.plot: As Queen reveals King's secret to Sanji, elsewhere as he is struggling against King, Zoro remembers an important fact from his past.

episodes.title: Secrets of Enma! The Cursed Sword Entrusted to Zoro
episodes.plot: Zoro still can't gain control of Enma which keeps extracting his Haki. Backed into a corner by the formidable King, Zoro remembers the encounter with an old man in his hometown when he was a child.

episodes.title: The Strike of an Ifrit! Sanji vs. Queen
episodes.plot: Queen's formidable attacks remind Sanji of his family. Annoyed by Queen's provocations, Sanji remembers a young woman mysteriously getting hurt in front of him and realizes what happened at that time, which lights a fire within him.

episodes.title: The Three-Sword Style of the Supreme King! Zoro vs. King
episodes.plot: As the battle between Zoro and King reaches its climax, Zoro, after figuring out the secret of King's abilities, uses his newfound power to create the King of Hell Three Sword Style.

episodes.title: Luffy on the Move! The Turning Point of a New Era!
episodes.plot: Usopp finds Kin'emon's upper body and the heavily wounded Kiku. However, they are surrounded by the Gifters and can't find a way out. Seeing the samurai giving up hope, Usopp remembers his determination.

episodes.title: Shuron Hakke! A Lawless Dragon Closing in on Luffy
episodes.plot: Kaidou uses a form of drunk fighting known as Shuron Hakke which makes the battle harder for Luffy. Meanwhile at Mary Geoise, the Five Elders discuss a particularly troublesome Devil Fruit.

episodes.title: The Destruction of the Alliance?! Fire up, the Will of the New Generation!
episodes.plot: Know what this is about? Be the first one to add a plot.

episodes.title: Recapping Fierce Fights! Zoro vs. A Lead Performer
episodes.plot: Sanji and Chopper narrate the events of what has occurred in the battle between Zoro and King so far.
